00:02:25.866 --> 00:02:30.731
We have the B squared.
You have the B squared.

00:02:30.731 --> 00:02:34.522
And then you have the two ABx.

00:02:34.522 --> 00:02:38.144
Two ABx right over there.

00:02:38.144 --> 00:02:42.578
So this section, this entire
section, we can rewrite

00:02:42.578 --> 00:02:44.762
as being we know it, what A and B are.

00:02:44.762 --> 00:02:49.696
A is four and B is three
so this is going to be

00:02:49.696 --> 00:02:54.349
Ax, so four x plus

00:02:54.349 --> 00:02:59.111
four x plus b, which we know to be three.

00:02:59.111 --> 00:03:02.455
That whole thing, that whole
thing squared, and now we

00:03:02.455 --> 00:03:06.274
can't forget this x out front
so we have that x out front.

00:03:06.274 --> 00:03:08.119
And we're done. We have
just factored this.

00:03:08.119 --> 00:03:09.919
We have just factored this completely.

00:03:09.919 --> 00:03:12.113
We could write it as x
times four x plus three

00:03:12.113 --> 00:03:13.832
